Class FacilitiesTest

java.lang.Object
com.example.potato1_events.FacilitiesTest
public class FacilitiesTest extends Object
Unit tests for the Facility model class.

These tests verify the correctness of the Facility class's constructors, getters, setters, and helper methods.

    • testRemoveEventId

      Tests the Facility.removeEventId(String) method.

      Ensures that an existing event ID is correctly removed from the eventIds list.

    • testRemoveNonExistentEventId

      public void testRemoveNonExistentEventId()
      Tests the Facility.removeEventId(String) method when removing a non-existent event ID.

      Verifies that attempting to remove an event ID that does not exist does not affect the eventIds list.

    • testSetEventIds_Null

      public void testSetEventIds_Null()
      Tests the Facility.setEventIds(List) method when setting the event IDs to null.

      Ensures that eventIds is initialized as an empty list to maintain data integrity.

    • testCreatedAt_Null

      public void testCreatedAt_Null()
      Tests that the createdAt field can be null when not explicitly set.

      Verifies that a new Facility instance without a creation timestamp has createdAt as null.
